        "create_time": 1757747291.081888,
        "update_time": null,
        "content": {
          "content_type": "text",
          "parts": [
            "That’s **Tifinagh script**, used for writing **Tamazight (Berber) languages** of North Africa.  \n\nThe phrase:  \n\n**ⵔⴰⵎⵉ ⴰⵙ ⵎⴻⵏⴰⴷ**  \ntransliterates as: **Rami as menad**.  \n\n- **ⵔⴰⵎⵉ (Rami)** → a name, “Rami.”  \n- **ⴰⵙ (as)** → means “is” (a copula).  \n- **ⵎⴻⵏⴰⴷ (menad)** → can mean “wise,” “happy,” or sometimes “enduring,” depending on the dialect.  \n\nSo the phrase roughly means:  \n👉 **“Rami is happy/wise”** (with nuance depending on context).  \n\nWould you like me to expand on the range of meanings of **menad** across Tamazight dialects?"
          ]
        },
        "status": "finished_successfully",
        "end_turn": true,
